text: So, since we got the Naya angel as the BAB, should the Brawl decks end up being everything but Naya?
Not sure. Gavin apparently said Chulane was added because the Bant Brawl Commander was rotating and these decks are supposed to be balanced against once another.
Yeah, so with the Elder Dragons rotating, they’ll want to fill the holes, and Rienne fill the Naya slot, and then the 4 decks would fill the other 4?
I wonder what the mana bases will be in these packs.
Its a logical line of thinking.
I wonder if they’re going to switch on and off between Shards and Wedges consistently as well, unless we go back to Tarkir, right?
In theory, the products should never be two colors, right?
Not necessarily.
I see no reason they couldn't be 2 color.
I think 2 color is probably simpler to design.
But it probably depends also upon how successful these products are, how much they commit to Brawl, and if they feel they need to push things to draw more players to the format.

They said that they want to use these products to fill gaps in Brawl. They al always slot 2 color legends into a set. It’s almost a guarantee at this point. They don’t usually get to do 3 color ones conversely
That’s the only reason why I’m thinking that way. Maybe we’ll get more 3 color legends in Standard sets? I’d be down. I love me some 3 colors

That’s probable between his statements about Chulane and your observation about Rienne, but to say that’s going to be the norm going forward is restricting.

Plus, as we’ve seen from Wizards’ design over the years, they don’t necessarily lean into three colors often.

It would definitely be restricting, but I would be surprised if that is the average avenue for them to jam some 3 color legends. It seems like the simplest solution, though I would t want that to be the ONLY place to put them

I’m sure we’ll see at least one per set, but it’ll also help them keep two color legends in vogue as well.
Even with GRN in Standard we only have 1 GR, UW, BW, and UR legend.
Sure, there are Planeswalkers, but what happens once Guilds rotates out next year?

Wizards can’t sustain itself through sets like Dominaria/ War consistently (in terms of going super deep.)

I’m not disagreeing with you by the way. Just playing advocate hard.
